PSA: Fat Tuesday is in one week from today.

That means you have 1 week to host your Pączki eating contests, 1 week to share a box with your co-workers, 1 final week to buy a box and hide them in your secret hiding place so you don't have to share with the family.

Whatever you do, know that they are made by hand each day, with extra love from Chef William. From his family to yours! Enjoy!

Happy Random Acts of Kindness Day!

Share your LOVE AND KINDNESS WITH US!! Let's embrace this movement, share our experiences and bathe in the goodness that is making other people happy! 
Did you make someone else happy? Did you witness an act of kindness that left an impression?

Share your kindness story with us in the comments below.

#RandomActsOfKindness #RAKDay #LoveIsAllYouNeed #CreateConnnection #RiseByLiftingOthers #CelebrateTheLittleThings

Our West Seattle location will be serving a special dinner offering for Valentine’s Day. Starting at 5:30pm and staying open late until 9:00, we will be serving this decadent Beef Wellington.

Medium cooked beef tenderloin & carmalized onions wrapped in puff pastry with a red wine juniper sauce and a salad of mizuma and fried shallots. Mmmmmmm.

We can debate the pronunciation, but no one can argue about how insanely delicious they are.

Chef William has been up all night, and will be up each night until Fat Tuesday, making fresh pączki.

They are now in all 3 shops, but come early, they go fast!

This year's offerings: chocolate, vanilla bean, raspberry, lemon, strawberries and cream, or caramel apple.
